     # Zrb v[0m[2m2 Migration Guide
     
     This guide details the breaking changes introduced in Zrb v2 and provides the necessary steps to migrate your application from[0m[2m v1. v2 introduces project-based organization, improved pagination, and enhanced security.
     
     ## 1. Base[0m[2m URL Versioning
     All API endpoints are now versioned. You must update your client configuration to use the `/v2[0m[2m/` prefix for all requests.
     
     **v1 (Before)**
     ```http
     GET /tasks
     ```
     
     **[0m[2mv2 (After)**
     ```http
     GET /v2/tasks
     ```
     
     ## 2. Authentication Header[0m[2m
     The authentication mechanism has transitioned to the standard Bearer token format. The `X-Auth-Token` header is[0m[2m deprecated and will return a `401 Unauthorized` error.
     
     **v1 (Before)**
     ```http
[0m[2mX-Auth-Token: <your_api_key>
     ```
     
     **v2 (After)**
     ```http
     Authorization[0m[2m: Bearer <your_api_token>
     ```
     
     ## 3. Task ID Type Change
     Task IDs[0m[2m have changed from auto-incrementing integers to UUID strings to better support distributed systems. Ensure your local data structures and database[0m[2m schemas are updated to handle string-based UUIDs.
     
     **v1 (Before)**
     ```json
     {
       "id[0m[2m": 42,
       "title": "Write tests"
     }
     ```
     
     **v2 (After)**[0m[2m
     ```json
     {
       "id": "a1b2c3d4-e5f6[0m[2m-7890-abcd-ef1234567890",
       "title[0m[2m": "Write tests"
     }
     ```
     
     ## 4. Field Renaming: `done` to `completed[0m[2m`
     The `done` field has been renamed to `completed` across all responses and request bodies for better clarity.[0m[2m
     
     **v1 (Before)**
     ```json
     {
       "title": "Ship v1",
       "done":[0m[2m true
     }
     ```
     
     **v2 (After)**
     ```json
     {
       "title": "Ship[0m[2m v1",
       "completed": true
     }
     ```
     
     ## 5. Required `project_id[0m[2m` for Task Creation
     Tasks must now be associated with a project. The `project_id` field is now mandatory when creating a[0m[2m new task; omitting it will result in a `422 Unprocessable Entity` error.
     
     **v1 (Before[0m[2m)**
     ```json
     POST /tasks
     {
       "title": "New task title"
     }
[0m[2m```
     
     **v2 (After)**
     ```json
     POST /v2/tasks
     {
       "title":[0m[2m "New task title",
       "project_id": "proj_abc123"
     }
[0m[2m```
     
     ## 6. Paginated List Responses
     The list endpoint (`GET /v2/tasks`) no longer returns a bare array[0m[2m. It now returns a paginated envelope to support large datasets efficiently.
     
     **v1 (Before)**
     ```json
     [
[0m[2m  {"id": 1, "title": "Buy milk", "done": false},
       {"id": 2,[0m[2m "title": "Ship v1", "done": true}
     ]
     ```
     
     **v2 (After)**[0m[2m
     ```json
     {
       "items": [
         {"id": "...", "title": "Buy milk[0m[2m", "completed": false},
         {"id": "...", "title": "Ship v1", "completed":[0m[2m true}
       ],
       "total": 2,
       "next_cursor": "cursor_xyz[0m[2m"
     }
     ```
     
